OAK TRAIL SOLAR, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Oak Trail Solar, LLC ("Oak Trail") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Oak Trail generating facility ("Oak Trail Facility").
Oak Trail is a solar generating facility located in Currituck County, North Carolina. The Oak Trail Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities within the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") region.
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Oak Trail's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Oak Trail Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Oak Trail's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Oak Trail shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $1,600,586.84 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $133,382.24
